{"type":"message","id":"dcbb7522","parentId":"52a19e01","timestamp":"2026-03-03T16:19:10.522Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `exec` tool was used to try and search notes, but it resulted in an error: \"Error: No such command 'search'\". This indicates that the `memo` command does not have a `search` subcommand, or it's not available in this environment.\n\nI need to check the available commands for the `memo` CLI. The `apple-notes` skill description states: \"Manage Apple Notes via the `memo` CLI on macOS (create, view, edit, delete, search, move, and export notes).\" This implies that a search functionality *should* exist.\n\nSince the direct `search` command failed, I should try listing all notes and then potentially filtering them, or see if there's another way to search using `memo`. A common pattern for CLIs is to list all items and then allow filtering, or to have a specific `show` or `view` command that can take an argument.\n\nLet's try listing all notes first to see the output format and available commands. If that doesn't work, I'll need to consult the `apple-notes` skill's documentation or try a different approach."},{"type":"text","text":"<final>I encountered an issue trying to search your notes. The `memo` command, used for managing Apple Notes, returned an error when I tried to use a `search` function.\n\nI will now try to list all your notes to see if I can find \"Notes for ORION\" that way.</final>\n"}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-2.5-flash-lite","usage":{"input":27275,"output":311,"cacheRead":27013,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":27586,"cost":{"input":0.0027275000000000003,"output":0.00012440000000000002,"cacheRead":0.0006753250000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0035272250000000006}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772554748234}}
