{"type":"message","id":"e279d29d","parentId":"0e5b9265","timestamp":"2026-03-03T16:19:30.456Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering Note Retrieval**\n\nI'm focusing on retrieving the \"Grocery list\" note using the `apple-notes` skill. I recall the `memo` command failed, so I'm now exploring the capabilities of `apple-notes` directly to achieve the desired note access and preparation for content summarization. I want to check for errors.\n\n\n**Exploring Memo's Options**\n\nI'm now investigating `memo --help` to understand the available commands. The previous attempt with `memo search` clearly failed. I'm hoping `memo --help` will reveal viable alternatives for listing or searching notes within the `apple-notes` context. If this doesn't work, I'll need to explore reading all notes and filtering, but that's less efficient.\n\n\n**Investigating CLI Commands**\n\nI'm now checking the `memo` CLI's help output. Previous attempts with `search` failed, and the skill documentation points to `memo`. I want to see if `list` is a viable subcommand, but I'm expecting it might not be. I am also preparing for a contingency to read all notes and filter them manually if all else fails. I will need to inform the user if the `memo` CLI doesn't offer a suitable listing or searching tool.\n\n\n**Analyzing Memo's Functionality**\n\nI'm now focusing on assessing the `memo` CLI. I'm starting with `memo --help` to understand its core functionalities, since the `search` command failed earlier. The `apple-notes` skill mentions this CLI, and I need to figure out how to leverage it to find the \"Grocery list\" note. If `memo --help` doesn't provide a way to list or search, I might need alternative strategies, or have to tell the user that this action isn't possible. I need to handle any unexpected error.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1772554770439_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"memo --help"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"googl